      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yes, absolutely! If your dad wants someone to protect his stuff if he gets sick, he absolutely needs to look at a **Durable Power of Attorney**. That is the *only* thing you should ask about regarding that specific situation.\n\nThink of it like this: a regular POA is like a **temporary babysitter** who only works while the dad is awake and sane. If the dad passes away or gets too confused, that babysitter just leaves, and the dad's stuff is left unattended. A durable POA is like a **forever babysitter** who is sworn to stay with the dad until the very last second, even if the dad is passed out or dead.\n\nBeyond just the POA itself, here are a few other critical things to ask your dad's lawyer about to make sure his estate is taken care of smoothly:\n\n1.  **Healthcare Proxy (Medical Power of Attorney):** This is the \"goblin doctor\" version of the POA. It gives the agent the legal right to make medical decisions for the dad if he can't speak for himself. Just like the financial agent, this agent needs to be durable so they can make those tough medical calls even if the dad is in",
